<title>BELGIUM: BBL H1 96 pft up 18 pct at 5.1 bln Bfr.</title>
<headline>BBL H1 96 pft up 18 pct at 5.1 bln Bfr.</headline>
<dateline>BRUSSELS 1996-09-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Six-months to June 30, 1996</p>
<p>(in billions of Belgian francs unless stated)</p>
<p>    Group net profit		  5.07  vs  4.30</p>
<p>    Cons net interest income *   26.40  vs 23.58</p>
<p>    Cons net other income *	17.83  vs 13.48</p>
<p>    Operating costs		  26.29  vs 23.54</p>
<p>    Gross operating income	 17.95  vs 13.53</p>
<p>    Write downs, provisions	 8.63  vs  6.10</p>
<p>    Taxes				 4.19  vs  3.00</p>
<p>NOTE - Bank Bruxelles Lambert is Belgium's third largest</p>
<p>bank. * Income lines restated vs. half-year 1995 accounts.</p>
<p>    Cons total assets		3,440  vs 3,085</p>
<p>    Cons customer deposits	 1,771  vs 1,552</p>
<p>    Cons deposits by other banks 1,392  vs 1,278</p>
<p>    Cons private sector credits  1,260  vs 1,095</p>
<p>    Cons public sector credits     804  vs   686</p>
<p>    Cons finance sector credits  1,200  vs 1,146</p>
<p>-- Brussels Newsroom +32 2 287 6810, Fax +32 2 230 7710</p>
